# Cursor Initial Exploration Prompt
# Paste this in Cursor chat ONCE when you first open the project

---

You are working on a fork of **Chatwoot** — an open-source omnichannel customer support platform (MIT License). This fork is customized for **HOF Immigration**, an immigration consultancy firm in Pakistan/UAE that uses WhatsApp to manage client cases.

## Your first task — Explore and understand this codebase:

**Step 1 — Read these files in order:**
1. `README.md` — project overview
2. `Gemfile` — all Ruby dependencies and versions
3. `package.json` — all Node/JS dependencies
4. `config/routes.rb` — all routes (understand the API structure)
5. `db/schema.rb` — full database schema (this is the source of truth for data models)
6. `Procfile` and `Procfile.dev` — how the app starts
7. `.env.example` — all required environment variables
8. `app/models/conversation.rb` — core model
9. `app/models/message.rb` — core model
10. `app/models/user.rb` — core model
11. `app/models/account.rb` — multi-tenancy model
12. `app/javascript/` — scan directory structure only, don't read every file

**Step 2 — After reading, generate:**

A. **SETUP_GUIDE.md** — Complete local development setup:
   - Exact versions of Ruby, Node, PostgreSQL, Redis needed
   - Every command to run in order (install → setup → start)
   - Common errors and fixes
   - How to run tests

B. **ARCHITECTURE.md** — How this app works:
   - Request flow (browser → Rails → DB)
   - How real-time messaging works (ActionCable/WebSockets)
   - How background jobs work (Sidekiq)
   - How WhatsApp integration works
   - How multi-tenancy works (accounts)
   - Frontend architecture (Vue.js components/stores)

**Step 3 — Rules you must follow for ALL future work:**

Read the `.cursorrules` file in the root of this project.
Acknowledge every rule and confirm you understand them.

**Step 4 — Identify HOF customization opportunities:**

Based on the codebase, identify the best places to add:
1. SLA alert job (agent hasn't replied in X hours → email admin)
2. HubSpot webhook sync (conversation resolved → HubSpot update)
3. Custom immigration case timeline

For each, tell me:
- Which existing files are most relevant
- What new files you'd create
- Any risks or conflicts with existing code

---

**Important rules for you:**
- This is open-source (MIT) — you CAN read all files freely
- When you encounter something unclear → search https://github.com/chatwoot/chatwoot/issues first
- When you need Chatwoot API docs → check https://developers.chatwoot.com
- When you need Rails docs → check https://api.rubyonrails.org
- NEVER modify `db/schema.rb` directly
- NEVER edit existing migration files
- NEVER touch the `enterprise/` directory
- If you are about to change a core model (conversation, message, user, account) → STOP and ask me first
- All HOF-specific code goes in `HOF::` namespace
- Commit all HOF changes on branch `hof-main` only

Start with Step 1 now. Read the files and report back what you found.